# Execution Bridge

## 1. Purpose

The discovery side of `.cursor/` (PRD → Feature Area → Scope Slice) ends at **`Status: ready-for-user-stories`**. The execution side begins at **User Story** and ends at a merged PR.

Without an explicit seam, every Scope Slice that reaches `ready-for-user-stories` falls off a cliff. This rule defines the bridge — what artifact gets written next, where it lives, who writes it, what gates it, and how it flows into code.

This rule complements:

- `.cursor/rules/00-siso.mdc` — request quality and CHAT/DISCOVERY/EXECUTION classification
- `.cursor/rules/feature-area-workflow.mdc` — the discovery hierarchy that ends at Scope Slice `ready-for-user-stories`
- `.cursor/rules/execution-loop.mdc` — the autonomous governance loop that **stops** at this seam (v0)
- `.cursor/checkers/implementation-readiness-checker.md` — the gate before `/implement`

---

## 2. Hierarchy (the full lifecycle)

```
Product
→ Feature Area              (docs/product/feature-areas/)
→ Scope Slice               (docs/product/scope-slices/)            — ends at ready-for-user-stories
─── execution bridge ───
→ User Story                (docs/execution/user-stories/)          — IS-NN: behavior the user can verify
→ Implementation Plan       (docs/execution/plans/)                 — IP-NN: architect's pre-code design
→ Patch Intent Summary      (chat artifact, no file)                — pre-write approval ladder
→ Code change               (zedos/nextjs_space/** or apps/** + packages/**)
→ Verification Report       (chat artifact)                         — typecheck/lint/test/build evidence
→ Review Report             (chat artifact)                         — adversarial review of the diff
→ Iteration Synthesis       (chat artifact)                         — shipped summary, QA steps, next work
→ Pull Request              (GitHub)                                — merged after CLEAR pr-readiness check
```

**Hard rule.** No level may be skipped. A change that lands in code without a User Story + Implementation Plan + Patch Intent Summary in the chat history is governance-non-compliant and must be reverted unless the user has explicitly waived the gate in writing for that specific change.

---

## 3. Artifact contracts

### 3.1 User Story

| Field | Source |
|---|---|
| Location | `docs/execution/user-stories/<fa-kebab>--<slice-kebab>--<story-kebab>.md` |
| Template | `.cursor/templates/execution/user-story.template.md` |
| ID | `US-<fa-kebab>--<slice-kebab>--<story-kebab>` |
| Parent | One Scope Slice file (linked) |
| Status | `draft` → `ready-for-implementation` |
| Required sections | Acceptance Criteria, Test Plan, Touched Files (predicted), Out-of-Scope, Open Questions, Decision References |
| Authored by | `architect` agent OR human; reviewed by `scope-critic` for product-scope creep |
| Gate before next step | `implementation-readiness-checker.md` Part A (US-01 — US-06) |

A User Story translates a Scope Slice's `Acceptance-Level Outcome` and `UX States` into testable, executable behavior. It does not name implementation files, frameworks, or APIs — those belong to the Implementation Plan.

### 3.2 Implementation Plan

| Field | Source |
|---|---|
| Location | `docs/execution/plans/<fa-kebab>--<slice-kebab>--<story-kebab>.plan.md` |
| Template | `.cursor/templates/execution/implementation-plan.template.md` |
| ID | `IP-<US-...>` (one-to-one with the parent User Story) |
| Parent | One User Story file (linked) |
| Status | `proposed` → `approved` → `executed` |
| Required sections | Approach, Touched Files (exact paths), Layers Affected (per `72-hexagonal-boundaries.mdc`), Contracts Changed, Migrations, Tests, Rollback, Risks |
| Authored by | `architect` agent — never `implementer` |
| Gate before next step | `implementation-readiness-checker.md` Part B (IP-01 — IP-08) |

The Implementation Plan is the only artifact where architecture, layer boundaries, and exact file paths first appear. Once approved, it is the contract that `implementer` follows. Deviations require a new Plan revision — silent improvisation is forbidden.

### 3.3 Patch Intent Summary (PIS)

| Field | Source |
|---|---|
| Location | Chat-only — never persisted as a file |
| Template | `.cursor/templates/execution/patch-intent-summary.template.md` (referenced verbatim) |
| Authored by | `implementer` agent immediately before the first code edit |
| Approval | `approved` (apply) / `preview` (show full diff first) / `cancel` (stop) — never `ok` |
| Gate before next step | Explicit user `approved` in the immediately preceding turn |

PIS is the execution-side analogue of the PRD `/prd update` Patch Intent Summary. It binds **"the next code edits I am about to make"** to **"the Plan that was approved"**. It is the only mechanism by which `implementer` is allowed to write to source trees.

### 3.4 Verification Report

| Field | Source |
|---|---|
| Location | Chat-only — optionally archived under `docs/execution/verification/` for audit |
| Template | `.cursor/templates/execution/verification-report.template.md` |
| Authored by | `verifier` agent — never `implementer` |
| Required evidence | typecheck, lint (boundaries enforced), test, build (per layout) |
| Gate before next step | All four steps PASS (see `.cursor/agents/execution/verifier.md` hard-stop conditions) |

### 3.5 Review Report

| Field | Source |
|---|---|
| Location | Chat-only — optionally archived under `docs/execution/reviews/` for audit |
| Template | `.cursor/templates/execution/review-report.template.md` |
| Authored by | `reviewer` agent (adversarial to `implementer`) |
| Gate before next step | `pr-readiness-checker.md` CLEAR |

### 3.6 Iteration Synthesis

| Field | Source |
|---|---|
| Location | Chat-only — never persisted as a file |
| Template | `.cursor/templates/execution/iteration-synthesis.template.md` |
| Authored by | `implementer` or `bugfix` agent — after the final successful iteration, before `/commit` |
| Required sections | What shipped (mapped to AC), How to QA (automated + manual), Next steps (follow-up US/Slice, status updates, suggested command) |
| Gate before next step | Emitted when verifier PASS + reviewer PASS or REVISE-without-criticals; required before recommending `/commit` |

The synthesis closes the `/implement` or `/fix` loop. It is cumulative across all iterations — not a repeat of the per-iteration summary. Source the QA section from the User Story Test Plan and Plan Tests; source follow-up work from Scope Slice Dependencies, Plan Out of Scope, and sibling User Stories.

