## 4. Where artifacts live (path-aware, pre- and post-migration)

The execution-side `docs/execution/` tree is **identical before and after the Turborepo migration**. Only the source code paths change.

| Layout | Source code paths | Governance paths |
|---|---|---|
| **Pre-migration** (today) | `zedos/nextjs_space/src/**`, `zedos/nextjs_space/app/**`, `zedos/nextjs_space/lib/**`, `zedos/nextjs_space/prisma/**` | `docs/execution/**`, `.cursor/**` |
| **Post-migration** (after Phase 3) | `apps/web/**`, `packages/**`, `services/**`, `prisma/**` | `docs/execution/**`, `.cursor/**` |

Implementation Plans must list **exact** Touched Files using the layout in effect at planning time. If the migration runs between plan approval and execution, the plan is invalidated and must be re-approved.

---

## 5. Inputs to the bridge (what every Scope Slice must already provide)

A `ready-for-user-stories` Scope Slice carries everything `architect` needs to write the User Story:

| Scope Slice section | Used by | Used as |
|---|---|---|
| `User Value` | architect | One-sentence story preamble |
| `Exact Boundary` (Included / Excluded) | architect | Story scope; auto-generated Acceptance Criteria seeds |
| `UX States` | architect | Acceptance Criteria states (empty, loading, success, error, edge) |
| `Data Touched` | architect | Predicted Touched Files in `application/` and `infrastructure/persistence/` |
| `Credit / Payment Impact` | architect | Whether the Plan must touch `infrastructure/payments/` and `domain/credits/` |
| `Sharing / Privacy Impact` | architect | Whether the Plan must touch share-link surfaces and `noindex` headers |
| `Feedback / Instrumentation Impact` | architect | Whether the Plan must add owner-milestone hooks |
| `Acceptance-Level Outcome` | architect | The behavioral assertion the Story formalizes |
| `Dependencies` | architect | Cross-Slice ordering constraints |
| `Blockers` | architect | If non-empty, refuse to start — route to `/feature-area refine-slice` |

If a Scope Slice is missing any of these for the chosen story scope, **stop and route back to `/feature-area refine-slice`**. Do not fabricate the missing section in the User Story.

